  • Field Details

    • sizeOutput

      public final Operand<TInt32> sizeOutput
      The size of the array.

    • dtype

      public final DataType dtype
      The type of the elements on the tensor_array.

    • elementShape

      public final org.tensorflow.ndarray.Shape elementShape
      The expected shape of an element, if known. Used to validate the shapes of TensorArray elements. If this shape is not fully specified, gathering zero-size TensorArrays is an error.

    • dynamicSize

      public final boolean dynamicSize
      A boolean that determines whether writes to the TensorArray are allowed to grow the size. By default, this is not allowed.

    • clearAfterRead

      public final boolean clearAfterRead
      If true (default), Tensors in the TensorArray are cleared after being read. This disables multiple read semantics but allows early release of memory.

    • identicalElementShapes

      public final boolean identicalElementShapes
      If true (default is false), then all elements in the TensorArray will be expected to have identical shapes. This allows certain behaviors, like dynamically checking for consistent shapes on write, and being able to fill in properly shaped zero tensors on stack -- even if the element_shape attribute is not fully defined.

    • tensorArrayName

      public final String tensorArrayName
      Overrides the name used for the temporary tensor_array resource. Default value is the name of the 'TensorArray' op (which is guaranteed unique).
